Nigerian-American rapper and fitness coach, Chigozie Alvin Anugwom popularly known as A-Bate is stepping into the fashion industry by launching ‘A-Bate Fitness’ clothing line. A-Bate who hails from Owerri, studied child development in Child development in Lacc College Los Angeles Community, in Los Angeles California where his clothing line with be situated. The Los Angeles-based entrepreneur announced that the clothing line would be officially launched as soon as things are put in place. A-Bate is set to work on a limited-edition collection of clothing and accessories with its straightforward designs such as t-shirts, socks, hats, hoodies, and other adult apparels. A-Bate seems to be making exploit with doing things aside from music. He recently dropped LV Gucci produced by DJ Snake.